tors too (although they are sort of named) are capable of spotting you.  Actual true safe spots are pretty slim these days also.  The pyramid in the maze springs to mind but most everywhere else has at least some nearby spawns.  It is a great place to hunt but a very challenging one and the loot is very rare indeed, although also very nice.  I'd recommend coming back in a bit. <p><center><b><font color=RED><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=78504>Celeris Tujimson</a><br>Assassin of The Nameless<br></font></b><font color=CYAN size=2><i>"The reverse side also has a reverse side." - Japanese Proverb</i> </font></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzarindantarga.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zarin Dantarga</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://siyni.homestead.com/files/Pics/thiefwin.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(4/26/02 12:07:35 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=14251.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Qu about the New CT - Rogues drop.</span><hr size=1> 55+ mobs see invis in CT.<br><br> <p><P><table border="0">  <tr>    <td>      <p><font face="verdana, arial" size="-1"><a href= http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=14121><FONT SIZE=-1><FONT COLOR="Black"><b>Siyni</b></a> <br><a href=http://www.legacyofsorrow.net><FONT SIZE=-2><FONT COLOR="Black">[ Legacy of Sorrow ]</a><br></font></td>  </table></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies.showNextMessage?topicID=14251.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a hre